When Being 'Too Small' Becomes Your Superpower

to me


I'm playing a game that offends a lot of people.


Because I always tell them that no matter how "too short" or "too small" they might be for their dreams...


They can still make it to the biggest stage in the world.


I mean...


Look at Yuki Kawamura the shortest active player in the NBA right now.
Download


And it didn't happen overnight.


It took a lifetime of understanding exactly who he is and what makes him special.


See, when everyone else was telling him to "be realistic," he was busy turning his size into his superpower.


While others saw limitations, he saw advantages.


Lower center of gravity? Better ball control.

Smaller frame? Quicker direction changes.

Less height? Harder to steal the ball from.


He knew exactly what he was meant to be a point guard who could slice through defenses like they weren't even there.


And that's why it worked.


Because he didn't just train he trained SMART.


Every single day, he wasn't just practicing basketball.

He was mastering the art of being unstoppable at HIS size.

He was perfecting moves that ONLY someone his size could pull off.


And sure, you may say others had it harder...


But try being told every single day that you're too small to play professional basketball.


Try being from Japan, where basketball isn't even close to being the main sport.


Try being the shortest guy on every court you step on.


Try having to prove yourself EVERY. SINGLE. TIME. you step onto the court.


No sane person would bet on someone with those odds, right?


So you see...


The easiest thing he could have done was say "I'm too short for basketball, this is impossible"...


Or he could shut up and start working.


And that's what he did.


He didn't just practice he obsessed.

He didn't just train he transformed.

He didn't just play he revolutionized what's possible at his size.


Now he's not just playing for the Memphis Grizzlies in the NBA...


He's showing everyone that your biggest "weakness" can become your greatest strength.


He's proving that it's not about fitting the mold it's about breaking it completely.


He's demonstrating that when you truly understand your unique advantages, nothing can stop you.


He never intended to become a symbol of defying odds, but his story has inspired countless others.


And I want the same thing to happen to you too .


I want you to experience that incredible moment when you prove everyone wrong and achieve what they said was impossible.


Because you deserve it.


Just like Kawamura proved your limitations are only as real as you allow them to be.


And the moment you start seeing your differences as advantages...


That's when everything changes.


That's when you become unstoppable.


Just like Yuki Kawamura.




You deserve it, 

Shane
